subSubSection.paragraph:
Idiosoma mcnamarai
has a known extent of occurrence of nearly 6,000 km2 [5,862 km2], and an area of occupancy within that range of <500 km2. Given: (i) this geographic range; (ii) the sampling effort that has occurred in surrounding areas as a result of a major biotic survey (see 
Keighery 2004
); (iii) the occurrence of the species at <10 severely fragmented sites; and (iv) the continuing decline in the area, extent and/or quality of habitat in the central-eastern Wheatbelt agricultural zone (
Laurance et al. 2011
), this species is considered Endangered (B1ab[iii] + B2ab[iii]). Further close assessment under both Criteria A and B will be crucial to the continued survival of this species.
